nt Western poetry.Poet Len Krisak's vibrant metric translation captures the music of Virgil's richly textured verse by employing rhyme and other sonic devices. The result is English poetry rather than translated prose. Presenting the English on facing pages with the original Latin, Virgil's Eclogues also features an introduction by scholar Gregson Davis that situates the poems in the time in which they were created.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCountry lifezRomevPoetry. 0aPastoral poetry, LatinvTranslations into English. 4aLiterature. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAncient Studies.  aClassics.  aCultural Studies.  aLiterature.1 aDavis, Gregson.1 aKrisak, Len.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook-Package Literaturez978311041354008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311045954840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978081220536740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812205367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812205367/original  a978-3-11-041345-8  Penn Press eBook Package Complete Collection  a978-3-11-041354-0  Penn Press eBook-Package Literature  a978-3-11-045954-8  University of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK